.TH "host1x_syncpt_wait" 9 "host1x_syncpt_wait" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
host1x_syncpt_wait \- wait for a syncpoint to reach a given value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" host1x_syncpt_wait
.BI "(struct host1x_syncpt *sp "  ","
.BI "u32 thresh "  ","
.BI "long timeout "  ","
.BI "u32 *value "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sp" 12
host1x syncpoint
.IP "thresh" 12
threshold
.IP "timeout" 12
maximum time to wait for the syncpoint to reach the given value
.IP "value" 12
return location for the syncpoint value
